==============================================================
  SECURITY FINDING NOTIFICATION  |  F-01  |  CRITICAL
==============================================================

Finding ID    : F-01
Severity      : CRITICAL
OWASP Ref     : API2:2023 — Broken Authentication
API Tested    : JSONPlaceholder (https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com)
Endpoint      : GET /users
Date Discovered: Mon, 27 Apr 2026
Analyst       : CrazyCoder

--------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------

The /users endpoint returns the complete user dataset — including full
names, email addresses, physical addresses, geographic coordinates, phone
numbers, and company metadata — without requiring any authentication.

A GET request sent with NO Authorization header receives a 200 OK response
containing all 10 user records. This is a complete authentication failure.

--------------------------------------------------------------
PROOF OF CONCEPT  (Evidence)
--------------------------------------------------------------

REQUEST SENT:
  Method:  GET
  URL:     https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users
  Headers: (none — zero Authorization header)

RESPONSE RECEIVED:
  Status:  HTTP/1.1 200 OK
  Body:
  [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "Leanne Graham",
      "username": "Bret",
      "email": "Sincere@april.biz",
      "address": {
        "street": "Kulas Light",
        "city": "Gwenborough",
        "geo": { "lat": "-37.3159", "lng": "81.1496" }
      },
      "phone": "1-770-736-8031 x56442",
      "website": "hildegard.org",
      "company": { "name": "Romaguera-Crowe" }
    },
    ... 9 additional full user records returned
  ]

EXPECTED: HTTP 401 Unauthorized
ACTUAL:   HTTP 200 OK with complete PII dataset — CRITICAL FINDING

--------------------------------------------------------------
BUSINESS IMPACT
--------------------------------------------------------------

1. Any internet user can harvest all customer PII in one unauthenticated
   request — names, emails, physical addresses, phone numbers, geo-coords.

2. Under India's DPDP Act 2023, this constitutes a reportable personal data
   breach. Mandatory notification and potential financial penalties apply.

3. Harvested emails are directly usable for phishing and spam campaigns
   targeting your customers.

4. Geo-coordinates expose home or workplace locations — a direct personal
   safety risk for your users.

--------------------------------------------------------------
REMEDIATION  (Priority: IMMEDIATE — fix before any production deployment)
--------------------------------------------------------------

Step 1: Add authentication middleware to all data-returning routes.
        Return HTTP 401 Unauthorized when no valid credential is present.

Step 2: FastAPI implementation example:
        @app.get('/users')
        async def get_users(token: str = Depends(verify_token)):
            return user_service.get_all_users()

Step 3: Audit every endpoint — confirm auth enforcement on all routes
        that return sensitive data.

Step 4: Write automated tests asserting 401 for unauthenticated calls
        to prevent future regression.

